es.\n44-\n45-## Usage\n46-\n47-### Creating a client\n48-The easiest way to create a client is:\n49-\n50-```java\n51-KubernetesClient client = new KubernetesClientBuilder().build();\n52-```\n53-\n54-`DefaultOpenShiftClient` implements both the `KubernetesClient` & `OpenShiftClient` interface so if you need the\n55-OpenShift extensions, such as `Build`s, etc then simply do:\n56-\n57-```java\n58-OpenShiftClient osClient = new KubernetesClientBuilder().build().adapt(OpenShiftClient.class);\n59-```\n60-\n61-### Configuring the client\n62-\n63-This will use settings from different sources in the following order of priority:\n64-\n65-* System properties\n66-* Environment variables\n67-* Kube config file\n68-* Service account token & mounted CA certificate\n69-\n70-System properties are preferred over environment variables. The following system properties & environment variables can be used for configuration:\n71-\n72-| Property / Environment Variable                                                                                 | Description                                                                                                                              | Default value                                         |\n73-|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|\n74-| `kubernetes.disable.autoConfig` / `KUBERNETES_DISABLE_AUTOCONFIG`                                               | Disable automatic configuration (KubernetesClient would not look in `~/.kube/config`, mounted ServiceAccount, environment variables or System properties for Kubernetes cluster information)                                                                                                         | `false`                                               |\n75-| `kubernetes.master` / `KUBERNETES_MASTER`                                                                       | Kubernetes master URL                                                                                                                    | `https://kubernetes.default.svc`                      |\n76-| `kubernetes.api.version` / `KUBERNETES_API_VERSION`                                                             | API version                                                                                                                              | `v1`                                                  |\n77-| `openshift.url` / `OPENSHIFT_URL`                                                                               | OpenShift master URL                                                                                                                     | Kubernetes master URL value                           |\n78-| `kubernetes.oapi.version` / `KUBERNETES_OAPI_VERSION`                                                           | OpenShift API version                                                                                                                    | `v1`                                                  |\n79-| `kubernetes.trust.certificates` / `KUBERNETES_TRUST_CERTIFICATES`                                               | Trust all certificates                                                                                                                   | `false`                                               |\n80-| `kubernetes.disable.hostname.verification` / `KUBERNETES_DISABLE_HOSTNAME_VERIFICATION`                         |                                                                                                                                          | `false`                                               |\n81-| `kubernetes.certs.ca.file` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CA_FILE`                                                         |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n82-| `kubernetes.certs.ca.data` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CA_DATA`                                                         |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n83-| `kubernetes.certs.client.file` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_FILE`                                                 |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n84-| `kubernetes.certs.client.data` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_DATA`                                                 |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n85-| `kubernetes.certs.client.key.file` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_KEY_FILE`                                         |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n86-| `kubernetes.certs.client.key.data` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_KEY_DATA`                                         |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n87-| `kubernetes.certs.client.key.algo` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_KEY_ALGO`                                         | Client key encryption algorithm                                                                                                          | `RSA`                                                 |\n88-| `kubernetes.certs.client.key.passphrase` / `KUBERNETES_CERTS_CLIENT_KEY_PASSPHRASE`                             |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n89-| `kubernetes.auth.basic.username` / `KUBERNETES_AUTH_BASIC_USERNAME`                                             |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n90-| `kubernetes.auth.basic.password` / `KUBERNETES_AUTH_BASIC_PASSWORD`                                             |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n91-| `kubernetes.auth.serviceAccount.token` / `KUBERNETES_AUTH_SERVICEACCOUNT_TOKEN`                                 | Name of the service account token file                                                                                                   | `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n92-| `kubernetes.auth.tryKubeConfig` / `KUBERNETES_AUTH_TRYKUBECONFIG`                                               | Configure client using Kubernetes config                                                                                                 | `true`                                                |\n93-| `kubeconfig` / `KUBECONFIG`                                                                                     | Name of the kubernetes config file to read                                                                                               | `~/.kube/config`                                      |\n94-| `kubernetes.auth.tryServiceAccount` / `KUBERNETES_AUTH_TRYSERVICEACCOUNT`                                       | Configure client from Service account                                                                                                    | `true`                                                |\n95-| `kubernetes.tryNamespacePath` / `KUBERNETES_TRYNAMESPACEPATH`                                                   | Configure client namespace from Kubernetes service account namespace path                                                                | `true`                                                |\n96-| `kubernetes.auth.token` / `KUBERNETES_AUTH_TOKEN`                                                               |                                                                                                                                          |                                                       |\n97-| `kubernetes.watch.reconnectInterval` / `KUBERNETES_WATCH_RECONNECTINTERVAL`                                     | Watch reconnect interval in ms                                                                                                           | `1000`                                                |\n98-| `kubernetes.watch.reconnectLimit` / `KUBERNETES_WATCH_RECONNECTLIMIT`                                           | Number of reconnect attempts (-1 for infinite)                                                                                           | `-1`                                                  |\n99-| `kubernetes.connection.timeout` / `KUBERNETES_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT`                                               | Connection timeout in ms (0 for no timeout)                                                                                              | `10000`                                               |\n100-| `kubernetes.request.timeout` / `KUBERNETES_REQUEST_TIMEOUT`                                     